  "en_snotes_yusuf": null,
  "en_snotes_asad": "The verb rakana comprises the concepts of inclining (in one's feelings or opinions) towards, as well as of relying on, someone or something, and cannot be translated by a single word; hence my composite rendering of the phrase la tarkanu. The use of the past tense in alladhina zalamu indicates - as is often the case in the Qur'an - deliberate and persistent evildoing; this term is, therefore, suitably rendered as \"those who are bent on evildoing\". According to Zamakhshari, the particle thumma at the beginning of this last clause does not signify a sequence in time (\"and then\" or \"afterwards\") but, rather, a stress on the impossibility (istib'ad) of their ever being succoured by God.",
